quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  14,35,"And when Abraham said, “My Lord ! make this city secure and save me and my sons from worshipping idols"
  14,36,"My Lord ! they have misled many of the mankind, so whoever follows me is of me and whoever disobeys me, then certainly You are Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  14,37,"Our Lord ! I have settled (some) of my off-spring in a valley without cultivation, near Your Sacred House, our Lord ! that they may establish worship (salat), so make the hearts of mankind to incline towards them, and provide them with fruits that they may be grateful"
  14,38,Our Lord ! You certainly know that which we hide and that which we make public and nothing is hidden from God (whether) in the earth or in the sky
  14,39,"Praise is due only for God Who has granted me in old age, Ishmael and Isaac, my Lord is certainly the Hearer of prayer"
  14,40,My Lord ! make me one who establishes worship (salat) and (also) from my offspring. Our Lord ! and accept my prayer
  14,41,Our Lord ! protectively forgive me and my parents and the believers on the day the account (of deeds) will be established.”